PN,31401
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782514094
OL,3,CShould the King live in the palace on
OL,4,Cwhich we just spent #370 million?
OL,6,FIt might seem like a strange question
OL,7,Fto ask about the Head of State of the
OL,8,FUnited Kingdom.
OL,10,FShould he (or she) live at one of the
OL,11,Fmost famous buildings in the world,
OL,12,Fparticularly after British taxpayers
OL,13,Fjust spent #369 million redeveloping
OL,14,Fthe place?
OL,16,FIt will still be the "home" of the
OL,17,FBritish Monarchy and the
OL,18,F"headquarters" of the Royal Family as
OL,19,Fan institution, but it will no longer
OL,20,Fbe the place where this King (or the
OL,21,Fnext one) plans to rest his head.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
