FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782514094
OL,3,CShould the King live in the palace on
OL,4,Cwhich we just spent #370 million?
OL,6,FWe should be clear, the private
OL,7,Fapartments make up only a small
OL,8,Fproportion of the space inside
OL,9,FBuckingham Palace.
OL,11,FIf you were ever to wander into some
OL,12,Frooms at random, you are much more
OL,13,Flikely to find yourself in an office
OL,14,Fof the human resources or finance
OL,15,Fteam, or the diary secretaries.
OL,17,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782514094
OL,3,CShould the King live in the palace on
OL,4,Cwhich we just spent #370 million?
OL,6,FBigger rooms are used to host official
OL,7,Ffunctions - like State Visits,
OL,8,Freceptions, big state banquets, and
OL,9,Fvisiting dignitaries or diplomats.
OL,11,FQueen Elizabeth's private living
OL,12,Fquarters were in the North Wing,
OL,13,Ffacing Green Park, and that suite of
OL,14,Frooms will still be available to the
OL,15,FKing and Queen when they do wish to
OL,16,Fuse them to "retire" or recharge.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782514094
OL,3,CShould the King live in the palace on
OL,4,Cwhich we just spent #370 million?
OL,6,FBut for the rest of his reign, however
OL,7,Flong or short that will be, King
OL,8,FCharles will return to his beloved
OL,9,Fhome at Clarence House, just further
OL,10,Falong The Mall, where he has lived
OL,11,Fsince 2003.
OL,13,FIt is the King's way of saying, as his
OL,14,Fmother often felt before him, that
OL,15,FBuckingham Palace feels much more like
OL,16,F"the office" than "a home".
OL,18,FAnd if anyone thought the future King
OL,19,FWilliam and Queen Consort will move
OL,20,Fback into London, they will also be
OL,21,Fdisappointed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782514094
OL,3,CShould the King live in the palace on
OL,4,Cwhich we just spent #370 million?
OL,6,FPrince William's office has let it be
OL,7,Fknown before that they plan to stay at
OL,8,Fhis family home, Forest Lodge in
OL,9,FWindsor, when the change of reign does
OL,10,Fhappen.
OL,12,FAt Buckingham Palace, the King's flag,
OL,13,Fthe Sovereign's Standard, will still
OL,14,Ffly atop the palace when he is in
OL,15,Fresidence in London.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782514094
OL,3,CShould the King live in the palace on
OL,4,Cwhich we just spent #370 million?
OL,6,FBut it does mean that when tourists
OL,7,Farrive at the gates of Buckingham
OL,8,FPalace, no longer will they be able to
OL,9,Fask "do you think they're at home?" as
OL,10,Fthey did for decades when Queen
OL,11,FElizabeth lived there.
OL,13,FIn truth, no recent monarch has ever
OL,14,Ffelt at home at Buckingham Palace.
OL,16,FThe late Queen was known to prefer to
OL,17,Fescape to Windsor whenever she could,
OL,18,Fand it's believed it was her wish to
OL,19,Fpass away at Balmoral Castle, which
OL,20,Fwas where she died in 2022.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782514094
OL,3,CShould the King live in the palace on
OL,4,Cwhich we just spent #370 million?
OL,6,FSo will it make any difference? Has
OL,7,Fanyone even noticed that no monarch
OL,8,Fhas lived at Buckingham Palace since
OL,9,Fthe late Queen was moved out of there
OL,10,Fin March 2020 at the start of the
OL,11,FCovid pandemic?
OL,13,FSenior royal aides say they will now
OL,14,Fbe able to look at plans to open the
OL,15,Fpalace to the public for longer
OL,16,Fperiods of the year, rather than just
OL,17,Fin the summer months, which has been
OL,18,Fthe case since tickets started being
OL,19,Fsold in 1993.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782514094
OL,3,CShould the King live in the palace on
OL,4,Cwhich we just spent #370 million?
OL,6,FThe King is known to be keen to open
OL,7,Fup royal residences to greater public
OL,8,Faccess.
OL,10,FAnd it's not as if ticket-holders ever
OL,11,Fget the chance to freely wander around
OL,12,Fthe private apartments in any case
OL,13,F(similar arrangements are in place at
OL,14,FWindsor, Balmoral, Sandringham and
OL,15,FHighgrove).
OL,17,FAnd is it sensible to demand that two
OL,18,Fsenior royals in their late seventies
OL,19,Fupend their life at Clarence House and
OL,20,Fmove back to Buckingham Palace, just
OL,21,Fbecause monarchs have done so before?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782514094
OL,3,CShould the King live in the palace on
OL,4,Cwhich we just spent #370 million?
OL,6,FBuckingham Palace has been the
OL,7,Fofficial residence of the monarch
OL,8,Fsince Queen Victoria moved into the
OL,9,Fthen Buckingham House in 1837.
OL,11,FShe added two extra wings to the
OL,12,Fbuilding and later a fourth (the most
OL,13,Ffamous one with the balcony) to
OL,14,Faccommodate her growing family and her
OL,15,Fwish that the monarch should be seen
OL,16,Fby her people.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782514094
OL,3,CShould the King live in the palace on
OL,4,Cwhich we just spent #370 million?
OL,6,FBut it will never be the living
OL,7,Fquarters of her great, great, great-
OL,8,Fgrandson, King Charles and his
OL,9,Fconsort, Queen Camilla - and nor the
OL,10,FKing after that.
OL,12,FThis is the Talking Royals - our
OL,13,Fweekly podcast about the royal family,
OL,14,Fwith ITV News Royal Editor Chris Ship
OL,15,Fand Producer Lizzie Robinson.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
